%section#intro
  %p Courier bot is a simple chatbot demo. Its aim is to enable people on the frontline to send text messages for quick and easy reporting to admins.

  %div#instructions
    To get started:
    %ul
      %li= "As a admin, register the user who will be texting (their name and phone number):"
      %li.simple-user-form
        = simple_form_for User.new, method: :post, html: {class: 'form-inline'} do |f|
          = f.input :name, label: 'Name: ', class: 'form-control mb-2 mr-sm-2'
          = f.input :phone_number, label: 'Phone number: ', placeholder: 'eg. +12223334444', class: 'form-control mb-2 mr-sm-2'
          = f.button :submit, 'Register', id: 'submit-new-user', class: 'btn btn-primary'
      %li Then as a user, text 'help me' to +15799771147 to see available commands.
      %li Start sending text messages (commands) to that same number and see them showing up underneath automatically.

%section#needsReports
  %h4 Needs &amp; Reports
  .container
    .row
      .col
        %table.table#needTable
          %thead
            %tr
              %th.col Needs
          %tbody
            - Need.order(id: :desc).limit(10).each do |need|
              = render 'shared/list_item', message: need

      .col
        %table.table#reportTable
          %thead
            %tr
              %th.col Reports
          %tbody
            - Report.order(id: :desc).limit(10).each do |report|
              = render 'shared/list_item', message: report

%hr

%section#lastWords
  %p= "Once you're done, go to the #{ link_to "User page", users_url } to delete the profile you created. Also, find out more #{ link_to "about Courier Bot and the idea behind this project", '#', data: {toggle: 'modal', target: '#aboutModal'} }.".html_safe

